---
---

<section id="features" class="headline">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="section-eyebrow reveal">Why it's different</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Built on the two things that actually matter over SSH.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub reveal">
      Everything else — panes, files, AI — sits on top of a session that
      survives and a network path that reaches. Get those two wrong and
      nothing else matters.
    </p>

    <div class="headline-grid">
      <article class="headline-card reveal">
        <div class="card-icon" style="color:var(--accent-text)">
          <svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <path d="M12 3v18M3 13h9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span class="headline-tag">The core differentiator</span>
        <h3>Real tmux control mode, not a reimplementation</h3>
        <p>
          Smart Terminal runs <code class="mono">tmux -CC</code> on the
          remote and renders panes natively in the desktop UI. Your session
          lives inside tmux itself — so it keeps running through laptop
          sleep, network drops, VPN hiccups, and app crashes. Reconnect and
          every pane, every scrollback line, every running process is
          exactly as you left it. No SSH keep-alive tricks, no session
          replay guesswork — the persistence is real because tmux's
          persistence is real.
        </p>
        <ul class="headline-points">
          <li>Survives sleep, disconnects, and app restarts</li>
          <li>Native multi-pane rendering, not a dumb terminal in a box</li>
          <li>Scrollback and running processes untouched on reconnect</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="headline-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="card-icon" style="color:var(--info)">
          <svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
            <rect x="2.5" y="9.5" width="5" height="5" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <rect x="9.5" y="3" width="5" height="5" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <rect x="16.5" y="16" width="5" height="5" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <path d="M7.5 10.8 11 6.6M13.5 7.4 17.5 15.8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="1 3.2"/>
            <path d="M16.4 14.4l1.4 1.9-2.2 0.9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span class="headline-tag" style="color:var(--info)">Reach anything</span>
        <h3>ProxyJump &amp; bastion-host SSH, built in</h3>
        <p>
          Production boxes usually aren't directly reachable — they sit behind a jump host. Smart Terminal treats multi-hop SSH as a first-class connection type: configure a ProxyJump chain once and each hop authenticates independently, exactly like your <code class="mono">~/.ssh/config</code> already expects.
        </p>
        <ul class="headline-points">
          <li>Chain through one or more bastion hosts</li>
          <li>Independent auth per hop — no shared-key shortcuts</li>
          <li>Same tmux persistence guarantees end-to-end</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .headline {
    background: var(--sidebar);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .headline-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 28px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .headline-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
  .headline-card {
    background: linear-gradient(165deg, var(--surface) 0%, var(--bg) 100%);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 36px 32px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .headline-card::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: -1px;
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(213,154,74,0.5), transparent 40%);
    -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#000 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#000 0 0);
    -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
    mask-composite: exclude;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .card-icon {
    width: 56px;
    height: 56px;
    border-radius: 14px;
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .headline-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .headline-card h3 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .headline-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 15.5px;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }
  .headline-card code {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }
  .headline-points {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .headline-points li {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: var(--text);
    padding-left: 24px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .headline-points li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 7px;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
</style>
